  <!-- 1. Two Sum -->
  <div class="problem-card">
    <div class="problem-card-header">
      <span class="problem-number">#1</span>
      <h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Two Sum</h3>
      <span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="problem-card-body">
      <div class="technique-row">
        <span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span>
        <span class="tag tag-blue">HashMap Lookup</span>
        <span class="tag tag-teal">Complement Search</span>
      </div>
      <div class="panel info">
        <span class="panel-icon">💡</span>
        <div class="panel-content">
          <strong>Approach — HashMap (One-Pass)</strong>
          Store each number and its index in a HashMap as you iterate. For each element, check if its complement (<code>target − current</code>) already exists in the map. This avoids the O(n²) brute-force nested loop by turning lookups into O(1).
        </div>
      </div>
      <table class="complexity-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single pass through the array</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>HashMap stores up to n entries</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Two Sum — HashMap</span></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.HashMap;
<span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Map;

<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="kw">int</span>[] <span class="fn">twoSum</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums, <span class="kw">int</span> target) {
        Map&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>, <span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; map = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">HashMap</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="kw">int</span> i = <span class="nm">0</span>; i &lt; nums.length; i++) {
            <span class="kw">int</span> complement = target - nums[i];
            <span class="kw">if</span> (map.containsKey(complement)) {
                <span class="kw">return new</span> <span class="kw">int</span>[]{map.get(complement), i};
            }
            map.put(nums[i], i);
        }
        <span class="kw">return new</span> <span class="kw">int</span>[]{};
    }
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 121 -->
  <div class="problem-card">
    <div class="problem-card-header">
      <span class="problem-number">#121</span>
      <h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock</h3>
      <span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="problem-card-body">
      <div class="technique-row">
        <span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span>
        <span class="tag tag-blue">Greedy</span>
        <span class="tag tag-teal">Single Pass / Running Min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="panel info">
        <span class="panel-icon">💡</span>
        <div class="panel-content">
          <strong>Approach — Greedy (Running Minimum)</strong>
          Track the minimum price seen so far and the best profit achievable. For each price, update the min price and check if selling today beats the current max profit. One pass, no extra space.
        </div>
      </div>
      <table class="complexity-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single pass</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two variables only</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock</span></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">maxProfit</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] prices) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> minPrice = <span class="tp">Integer</span>.MAX_VALUE;
        <span class="kw">int</span> maxProfit = <span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="kw">int</span> price : prices) {
            <span class="kw">if</span> (price &lt; minPrice) {
                minPrice = price;
            }
            <span class="kw">else if</span> (price - minPrice &gt; maxProfit) {
                maxProfit = price - minPrice;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> maxProfit;
    }
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

