    <div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#53</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Maximum Subarray</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div>
    <div class="problem-card-body">
      <div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Kadane's Algorithm</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Dynamic Programming (1D)</span></div>
      <div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Kadane's Algorithm</strong>Maintain a running sum. At each step: <code>currentSum = max(nums[i], currentSum + nums[i])</code>. If adding the current element makes the sum worse than starting fresh, restart. Track the global maximum.</div></div>
      <table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two variables</td></tr></tbody></table>
      <div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Maximum Subarray — Kadane's</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">maxSubArray</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> maxSum = nums[<span class="nm">0</span>], currentSum = nums[<span class="nm">0</span>];
        <span class="kw">for</span> (<span class="kw">int</span> i = <span class="nm">1</span>; i &lt; nums.length; i++) {
            currentSum = <span class="tp">Math</span>.max(nums[i], currentSum + nums[i]);
            maxSum = <span class="tp">Math</span>.max(maxSum, currentSum);
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> maxSum;
    }
}</pre></div>
