    <div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#11</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Container With Most Water</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div>
    <div class="problem-card-body">
      <div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Two Pointers</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Greedy Pointer Shrink</span></div>
      <div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Two Pointers (Shrink Smaller Side)</strong>Start with the widest container. Moving the taller pointer inward can only reduce area (width decreases, height can't improve). So always move the shorter pointer inward to search for a taller one.</div></div>
      <table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two pointers only</td></tr></tbody></table>
      <div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Container With Most Water</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">maxArea</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] height) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> left = <span class="nm">0</span>, right = height.length - <span class="nm">1</span>, max = <span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span> (left &lt; right) {
            max = <span class="tp">Math</span>.max(max, <span class="tp">Math</span>.min(height[left], height[right]) * (right-left));
            <span class="kw">if</span> (height[left] &lt; height[right]) {
                left++;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span> {
                right--;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> max;
    }
}</pre></div>
