      <div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Horizontal Scanning</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Iterative Trimming</span></div>
      <div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Horizontal Scan (Trim Prefix)</strong>Take the first string as the initial prefix. Compare it with each next string, trimming one character at a time from the end until it matches the start of that string.</div></div>
      <table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(S)</td><td>S = total chars across all strings</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>In-place prefix trimming</td></tr></tbody></table>
      <div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Longest Common Prefix</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">String</span> <span class="fn">longestCommonPrefix</span>(<span class="tp">String</span>[] strs) {
        <span class="tp">String</span> prefix = strs[<span class="nm">0</span>];
