      <div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Concatenation + Containment Check</strong>Concatenate s with itself → <code>s+s</code>. Remove the first and last characters. If s appears in the result, s can be formed by repeating a substring. This leverages the rotational symmetry property of repeated-pattern strings.</div></div>
      <table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n²)</td><td>contains() worst case</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Doubled string</td></tr></tbody></table>
      <div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Repeated Substring Pattern</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
