  <h2 class="section-heading" id="linked-lists"><span class="section-icon">L</span> Linked Lists</h2>
  <div class="panel note"><span class="panel-icon">📌</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>ListNode definition (assumed for all problems below)</strong><br><code>class ListNode { int val; ListNode next; ListNode(int v){ val=v; } }</code></div></div>

  <!-- All 8 linked list problems -->
  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#206</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Reverse Linked List</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Iterative Pointer Reversal</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Three Pointer (prev/curr/next)</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Three-Pointer Iterative Reversal</strong>Maintain prev (null), curr, and a saved next. At each step point curr.next → prev, advance all three pointers. When curr is null, prev is the new head.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Three pointers</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Reverse Linked List</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">reverseList</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> head) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> prev=<span class="kw">null</span>, curr=head;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(curr!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
            <span class="tp">ListNode</span> next=curr.next; curr.next=prev; prev=curr; curr=next;
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> prev;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#21</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Merge Two Sorted Lists</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Two Pointers</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Dummy Head Node</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Dummy Head + Two Pointer Merge</strong>A dummy head node eliminates special-casing the result head. Walk both lists, always attaching the smaller node. Append the remaining list at the end.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m+n)</td><td>Visit every node once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>In-place linking</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Merge Two Sorted Lists</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">mergeTwoLists</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> l1, <span class="tp">ListNode</span> l2) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> dummy=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span>(<span class="nm">0</span>), cur=dummy;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(l1!=<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;l2!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
            <span class="kw">if</span>(l1.val&lt;=l2.val){cur.next=l1;l1=l1.next;}<span class="kw">else</span>{cur.next=l2;l2=l2.next;}
            cur=cur.next;
        }
        cur.next=(l1!=<span class="kw">null</span>)?l1:l2;
        <span class="kw">return</span> dummy.next;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#19</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Remove Nth Node From End of List</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Two Pointers (Fast &amp; Slow)</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Gap Technique</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — n-Gap Two Pointers</strong>Advance the fast pointer n+1 steps ahead. Then move both together until fast is null. Slow pointer lands just before the node to remove.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>One pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two pointers</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Remove Nth Node From End</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">removeNthFromEnd</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> head, <span class="kw">int</span> n) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> dummy=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span>(<span class="nm">0</span>); dummy.next=head;
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> fast=dummy, slow=dummy;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;=n;i++) fast=fast.next;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(fast!=<span class="kw">null</span>){fast=fast.next;slow=slow.next;}
        slow.next=slow.next.next;
        <span class="kw">return</span> dummy.next;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#141</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Linked List Cycle</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Floyd's Cycle Detection</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Fast &amp; Slow Pointers (Tortoise &amp; Hare)</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Floyd's Algorithm</strong>Slow pointer moves 1 step, fast moves 2. If there's a cycle, they will meet. If fast reaches null, no cycle exists. No extra memory needed — no HashSet of visited nodes.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>They meet within one cycle length</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two pointers only</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Linked List Cycle — Floyd's</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">hasCycle</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> head) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> slow=head, fast=head;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(fast!=<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;fast.next!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
            slow=slow.next; fast=fast.next.next;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(slow==fast) {
                 <span class="kw">return true</span>;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return false</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#2</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Add Two Numbers</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Simulation</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Carry Propagation</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Digit-by-Digit Simulation with Carry</strong>Traverse both lists in parallel. At each position, sum the digits plus carry. Create a new node for (sum % 10) and pass (sum / 10) as carry to the next iteration. Handle leftover nodes and final carry.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(max(m,n))</td><td>Traverse longer list</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(max(m,n))</td><td>New result list</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Add Two Numbers</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">addTwoNumbers</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> l1, <span class="tp">ListNode</span> l2) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> dummy=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span>(<span class="nm">0</span>), cur=dummy; <span class="kw">int</span> carry=<span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(l1!=<span class="kw">null</span>||l2!=<span class="kw">null</span>||carry!=<span class="nm">0</span>) {
            <span class="kw">int</span> sum=carry;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(l1!=<span class="kw">null</span>){sum+=l1.val;l1=l1.next;}
            <span class="kw">if</span>(l2!=<span class="kw">null</span>){sum+=l2.val;l2=l2.next;}
            carry=sum/<span class="nm">10</span>; cur.next=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span>(sum%<span class="nm">10</span>); cur=cur.next;
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> dummy.next;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#160</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Intersection of Two Linked Lists</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Two Pointers (Path Equalization)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Redirect on Null</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Dual Path Traversal</strong>Two pointers walk both lists. When one reaches the end, redirect to the other list's head. After traversing a+b total nodes, both pointers are equidistant from the intersection (or both null if no intersection).</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m+n)</td><td>Each pointer walks both lists</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>No extra storage</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Intersection of Two Linked Lists</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">getIntersectionNode</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> headA, <span class="tp">ListNode</span> headB) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> a=headA, b=headB;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(a!=b) { a=(a==<span class="kw">null</span>)?headB:a.next; b=(b==<span class="kw">null</span>)?headA:b.next; }
        <span class="kw">return</span> a;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#234</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Palindrome Linked List</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Fast &amp; Slow Pointers</span><span class="tag tag-purple">In-Place Reversal</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Find Mid → Reverse Second Half → Compare</strong>Use slow/fast pointers to find the midpoint. Reverse the second half in-place. Compare both halves from outside in. Achieves O(1) space — better than copying to an array.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Find mid + reverse + compare</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>In-place reverse</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Palindrome Linked List</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">isPalindrome</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> head) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> slow=head,fast=head;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(fast!=<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;fast.next!=<span class="kw">null</span>){slow=slow.next;fast=fast.next.next;}
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> prev=<span class="kw">null</span>,cur=slow;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(cur!=<span class="kw">null</span>){<span class="tp">ListNode</span> nx=cur.next;cur.next=prev;prev=cur;cur=nx;}
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> l=head,r=prev;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(r!=<span class="kw">null</span>){<span class="kw">if</span>(l.val!=r.val)<span class="kw">return false</span>;l=l.next;r=r.next;}
        <span class="kw">return true</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#25</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Reverse Nodes in k-Group</h3><span class="tag tag-red">Hard</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Recursion</span><span class="tag tag-purple">In-Place k-Group Reversal</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Recursive Group Reversal</strong>Check if k nodes remain. If so, reverse them and recursively process the rest. The reversed group's tail points to the result of the recursive call. If fewer than k nodes remain, return them unchanged.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Each node reversed once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n/k)</td><td>Recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Reverse Nodes in k-Group</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">ListNode</span> <span class="fn">reverseKGroup</span>(<span class="tp">ListNode</span> head, <span class="kw">int</span> k) {
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> cur=head; <span class="kw">int</span> count=<span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(cur!=<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;count&lt;k){cur=cur.next;count++;}
        <span class="kw">if</span>(count&lt;k) {
                 <span class="kw">return</span> head;
            }
        <span class="tp">ListNode</span> prev=<span class="kw">null</span>; cur=head;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;k;i++){<span class="tp">ListNode</span> nx=cur.next;cur.next=prev;prev=cur;cur=nx;}
        head.next=<span class="fn">reverseKGroup</span>(cur,k);
        <span class="kw">return</span> prev;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

