  <h2 class="section-heading" id="stacks-queues"><span class="section-icon">SQ</span> Stacks &amp; Queues</h2>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#232</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Implement Queue using Stacks</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Two-Stack Queue Simulation</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Amortized Analysis</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Two Stacks (Lazy Transfer)</strong>Push to stack1. On pop/peek, transfer all elements to stack2 only if it's empty. Elements in stack2 are already reversed into FIFO order. Each element is moved at most once → amortized O(1) per operation.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(1) amortized</td><td>Each element transferred once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Two stacks combined</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Queue using Stacks</span></div><pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Stack;
<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">MyQueue</span> {
    <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; in=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;(), out=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="kw">public void</span> push(<span class="kw">int</span> x){in.push(x);}
    <span class="kw">public int</span> pop(){move();<span class="kw">return</span> out.pop();}
    <span class="kw">public int</span> peek(){move();<span class="kw">return</span> out.peek();}
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> empty(){<span class="kw">return</span> in.isEmpty()&amp;&amp;out.isEmpty();}
    <span class="kw">private void</span> move(){<span class="kw">if</span>(out.isEmpty() {
                )<span class="kw">while</span>(!in.isEmpty())out.push(in.pop());
            }}
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#225</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Implement Stack using Queues</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Queue Rotation Simulation</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Single Queue with Rotation on Push</strong>After enqueuing the new element, rotate all previous elements to the back of the queue. The new element is now at the front, simulating LIFO. Pop and peek are then just queue poll/peek.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">push O(n), pop O(1)</td><td>Rotation cost on push</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>One queue</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Stack using Queues</span></div><pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.*;
<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">MyStack</span> {
    <span class="tp">Queue</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; q=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">LinkedList</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="kw">public void</span> push(<span class="kw">int</span> x){
        q.offer(x);
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;q.size()-<span class="nm">1</span>;i++) q.offer(q.poll());
    }
    <span class="kw">public int</span> pop(){<span class="kw">return</span> q.poll();}
    <span class="kw">public int</span> top(){<span class="kw">return</span> q.peek();}
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> empty(){<span class="kw">return</span> q.isEmpty();}
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#739</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Daily Temperatures</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Monotonic Stack</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Next Greater Element Pattern</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Monotonic Decreasing Stack</strong>Store indices in a stack that is always decreasing in temperature. When a warmer day is found, pop all cooler days from the stack and compute the wait distance. This is the classic "Next Greater Element" pattern.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Each index pushed/popped once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Stack</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Daily Temperatures — Monotonic Stack</span></div><pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Stack;
<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span>[] <span class="fn">dailyTemperatures</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] temperatures) {
        <span class="kw">int</span>[] res=<span class="kw">new int</span>[temperatures.length];
        <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; st=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;temperatures.length;i++){
            <span class="kw">while</span>(!st.isEmpty()&amp;&amp;temperatures[i]&gt;temperatures[st.peek()])
                res[st.peek()]=i-st.pop();
            st.push(i);
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> res;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#496</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Next Greater Element I</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Monotonic Stack</span><span class="tag tag-teal">HashMap Precomputation</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Monotonic Stack + HashMap</strong>Precompute next-greater mappings for all nums2 elements using a monotonic stack. Store results in a HashMap. Then answer each nums1 query in O(1) with a map lookup.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m+n)</td><td>One pass each</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>HashMap + stack</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Next Greater Element I</span></div><pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.*;
<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span>[] <span class="fn">nextGreaterElement</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums1,<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums2) {
        <span class="tp">Map</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>,<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; map=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">HashMap</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; st=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n:nums2){<span class="kw">while</span>(!st.isEmpty()&amp;&amp;st.peek()&lt;n)map.put(st.pop(),n);st.push(n);}
        <span class="kw">int</span>[] res=<span class="kw">new int</span>[nums1.length];
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;nums1.length;i++) res[i]=map.getOrDefault(nums1[i],-<span class="nm">1</span>);
        <span class="kw">return</span> res;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#155</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Min Stack</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Auxiliary Min Stack</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Parallel Stack Design</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Two-Stack Design (Main + Min)</strong>Maintain a parallel min-stack that only updates when the pushed value is ≤ current minimum. Both stacks stay in sync — pop from min-stack only when the popped main-stack value equals the current min.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(1) all ops</td><td>Constant-time push/pop/getMin</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Two stacks</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Min Stack</span></div><pre><span class="kw">import</span> java.util.Stack;
<span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">MinStack</span> {
    <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; stack=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;(), minStack=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="kw">public void</span> push(<span class="kw">int</span> val){
        stack.push(val);
        <span class="kw">if</span>(minStack.isEmpty() {
                ||val&lt;
            }=minStack.peek()) minStack.push(val);
    }
    <span class="kw">public void</span> pop(){ <span class="kw">if</span>(stack.pop() {
                .equals(minStack.peek())) minStack.pop();
            } }
    <span class="kw">public int</span> top(){ <span class="kw">return</span> stack.peek(); }
    <span class="kw">public int</span> getMin(){ <span class="kw">return</span> minStack.peek(); }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <!-- ═══ BINARY SEARCH ═══ -->
  <h2 class="section-heading" id="binary-search"><span class="section-icon">B</span> Binary Search</h2>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#704</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Binary Search</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Classic Binary Search</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Divide &amp; Conquer</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Iterative Binary Search</strong>Maintain left and right bounds. Compute mid with <code>lo + (hi-lo)/2</code> (avoids overflow). Compare and halve the search space each iteration until target is found or bounds cross.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log n)</td><td>Halve each step</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Iterative</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Binary Search</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">search</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums,<span class="kw">int</span> target) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> lo=<span class="nm">0</span>, hi=nums.length-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;=hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[mid]==target)<span class="kw">return</span> mid;
            <span class="kw">else if</span>(nums[mid]&lt;target) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> -<span class="nm">1</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#34</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Find First and Last Position in Sorted Array</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Binary Search (Left &amp; Right Bound)</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Two Separate Binary Searches</strong>First search: when target found, record it and continue searching left (hi = mid-1). Second search: when target found, record it and continue searching right (lo = mid+1). Returns first and last occurrence.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log n)</td><td>Two binary searches</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Iterative</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">First and Last Position</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span>[] <span class="fn">searchRange</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums,<span class="kw">int</span> target){
        <span class="kw">return new int</span>[]{<span class="fn">find</span>(nums,target,<span class="kw">true</span>),<span class="fn">find</span>(nums,target,<span class="kw">false</span>)};
    }
    <span class="kw">private int</span> <span class="fn">find</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums,<span class="kw">int</span> t,<span class="kw">boolean</span> first){
        <span class="kw">int</span> lo=<span class="nm">0</span>,hi=nums.length-<span class="nm">1</span>,idx=-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;=hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[mid]==t){idx=mid;<span class="kw">if</span>(first) {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }<span class="kw">else</span> {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }}
            <span class="kw">else if</span>(nums[mid]&lt;t) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            <span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> idx;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#74</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Search a 2D Matrix</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Binary Search on Virtual 1D Array</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Flatten to 1D Binary Search</strong>Treat the m×n matrix as a sorted 1D array of m*n elements. For mid index, convert to row = mid/cols and col = mid%cols to access the actual matrix element.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log(m·n))</td><td>Binary search on flattened</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>No extra space</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Search 2D Matrix</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">searchMatrix</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[][] matrix,<span class="kw">int</span> target) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> rows=matrix.length, cols=matrix[<span class="nm">0</span>].length, lo=<span class="nm">0</span>, hi=rows*cols-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;=hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>, val=matrix[mid/cols][mid%cols];
            <span class="kw">if</span>(val==target)<span class="kw">return true</span>;<span class="kw">else if</span>(val&lt;target) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }<span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return false</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#33</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Search in Rotated Sorted Array</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Binary Search with Rotation Detection</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Identify Sorted Half, Then Binary Search</strong>In each iteration, at least one half (left or right of mid) is always sorted. Compare target against that sorted half's range to decide which side to search next.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log n)</td><td>Standard binary search</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Iterative</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Search Rotated Array</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">search</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums,<span class="kw">int</span> target){
        <span class="kw">int</span> lo=<span class="nm">0</span>,hi=nums.length-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;=hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[mid]==target)<span class="kw">return</span> mid;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[lo]&lt;=nums[mid]){
                <span class="kw">if</span>(target&gt;=nums[lo]&amp;&amp;target&lt;nums[mid]) {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            } <span class="kw">else</span> {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            }<span class="kw">else</span>{
                <span class="kw">if</span>(target&gt;nums[mid]&amp;&amp;target&lt;=nums[hi]) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            } <span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> -<span class="nm">1</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#81</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Search in Rotated Sorted Array II</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Binary Search with Duplicate Handling</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Rotation Search + Duplicate Skip</strong>Same as #33 but when <code>nums[lo] == nums[mid]</code>, we can't determine which half is sorted — so increment lo by 1 to skip the duplicate. This degrades worst-case to O(n) when all elements are the same.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log n) avg, O(n) worst</td><td>Duplicates cause linear scan</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Iterative</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Search Rotated Array II (with Duplicates)</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">search</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums,<span class="kw">int</span> target){
        <span class="kw">int</span> lo=<span class="nm">0</span>,hi=nums.length-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;=hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[mid]==target)<span class="kw">return true</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[lo]==nums[mid]){lo++;<span class="kw">continue</span>;}
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[lo]&lt;nums[mid]){
                <span class="kw">if</span>(target&gt;=nums[lo]&amp;&amp;target&lt;nums[mid]) {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }<span class="kw">else</span> {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            }<span class="kw">else</span>{
                <span class="kw">if</span>(target&gt;nums[mid]&amp;&amp;target&lt;=nums[hi]) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }<span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid-<span class="nm">1</span>;
            }
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return false</span>;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#162</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Find Peak Element</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Binary Search on Slope</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Binary Search on Ascending Slope</strong>If <code>nums[mid] &lt; nums[mid+1]</code>, we're on an ascending slope and a peak must exist to the right. Otherwise peak is at mid or to the left. Converges to a peak in O(log n).</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(log n)</td><td>Slope-based halving</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Iterative</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Find Peak Element</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">findPeakElement</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
        <span class="kw">int</span> lo=<span class="nm">0</span>,hi=nums.length-<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">while</span>(lo&lt;hi){
            <span class="kw">int</span> mid=lo+(hi-lo)/<span class="nm">2</span>;
            <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[mid]&lt;nums[mid+<span class="nm">1</span>]) {
                lo=mid+<span class="nm">1</span>;
            } <span class="kw">else</span> {
                hi=mid;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> lo;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <!-- ═══ TREES ═══ -->
  <h2 class="section-heading" id="trees"><span class="section-icon">T</span> Trees</h2>
  <div class="panel note"><span class="panel-icon">📌</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>TreeNode definition (assumed for all tree problems)</strong><br><code>class TreeNode { int val; TreeNode left, right; TreeNode(int v){ val=v; } }</code></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#104</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Maximum Depth of Binary Tree</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">DFS (Recursive)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Divide &amp; Conquer</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Recursive DFS (Post-Order)</strong>maxDepth(node) = 1 + max(maxDepth(left), maxDepth(right)). Base case: null returns 0. Classic divide-and-conquer on a tree.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Visit every node</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(h)</td><td>h = tree height (recursion stack)</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">maxDepth</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root) {
        <span class="kw">if</span>(root==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">1</span>+<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(<span class="fn">maxDepth</span>(root.left),<span class="fn">maxDepth</span>(root.right));
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#100</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Same Tree</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">DFS (Recursive)</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Structural Comparison</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Recursive Structural Equivalence</strong>Base: both null → true, one null → false, values differ → false. Recurse on both subtrees simultaneously.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Visit every node</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(h)</td><td>Call stack</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">isSameTree</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> p,<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> q){
        <span class="kw">if</span>(p==<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;q==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return true</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span>(p==<span class="kw">null</span>||q==<span class="kw">null</span>||p.val!=q.val)<span class="kw">return false</span>;
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="fn">isSameTree</span>(p.left,q.left)&amp;&amp;<span class="fn">isSameTree</span>(p.right,q.right);
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#101</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Symmetric Tree</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">DFS (Mirror Check)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Recursive Symmetry</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Mirror Recursion</strong>Check isMirror(left, right): values equal AND left.left mirrors right.right AND left.right mirrors right.left. Elegant two-pointer DFS on opposite sides of the tree.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Each node visited once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(h)</td><td>Recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">isSymmetric</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){<span class="kw">return</span> <span class="fn">mirror</span>(root.left,root.right);}
    <span class="kw">boolean</span> <span class="fn">mirror</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> l,<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> r){
        <span class="kw">if</span>(l==<span class="kw">null</span>&amp;&amp;r==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return true</span>;
        <span class="kw">if</span>(l==<span class="kw">null</span>||r==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return false</span>;
        <span class="kw">return</span> l.val==r.val&amp;&amp;<span class="fn">mirror</span>(l.left,r.right)&amp;&amp;<span class="fn">mirror</span>(l.right,r.left);
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#144 / #94 / #145</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Tree Traversals (Pre / In / Post order)</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">DFS Iterative (Stack)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Preorder / Inorder / Postorder</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Preorder (Root→L→R):</strong> Push root, pop+record, push right then left.<br><strong>Inorder (L→Root→R):</strong> Push nodes left-ward, pop+record when null, go right.<br><strong>Postorder (L→R→Root):</strong> Modified preorder (Root→R→L), add to front of LinkedList.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Traversal</th><th>Time</th><th>Space</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>All three</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">All Three Traversals</span></div><pre><span class="cm">// PREORDER</span>
<span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="fn">preorder</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){
    <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">TreeNode</span>&gt; st=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="kw">if</span>(root!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(root);
            }
    <span class="kw">while</span>(!st.isEmpty()){<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> n=st.pop();res.add(n.val);
        <span class="kw">if</span>(n.right!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(n.right);
            } <span class="kw">if</span>(n.left!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(n.left);
            }}
    <span class="kw">return</span> res;
}
<span class="cm">// INORDER</span>
<span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="fn">inorder</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){
    <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">TreeNode</span>&gt; st=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;(); <span class="tp">TreeNode</span> cur=root;
    <span class="kw">while</span>(cur!=<span class="kw">null</span>||!st.isEmpty()){
        <span class="kw">while</span>(cur!=<span class="kw">null</span>){st.push(cur);cur=cur.left;}
        cur=st.pop();res.add(cur.val);cur=cur.right;
    }
    <span class="kw">return</span> res;
}
<span class="cm">// POSTORDER</span>
<span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; <span class="fn">postorder</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){
    <span class="tp">LinkedList</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">LinkedList</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;<span class="tp">TreeNode</span>&gt; st=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">Stack</span>&lt;&gt;();
    <span class="kw">if</span>(root!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(root);
            }
    <span class="kw">while</span>(!st.isEmpty()){<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> n=st.pop();res.addFirst(n.val);
        <span class="kw">if</span>(n.left!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(n.left);
            } <span class="kw">if</span>(n.right!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                st.push(n.right);
            }}
    <span class="kw">return</span> res;
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#102</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Binary Tree Level Order Traversal</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">BFS (Level-by-Level)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Queue with Size Snapshot</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — BFS with Level Snapshots</strong>Use a queue. At each level, snapshot the queue size, process exactly that many nodes, collect their values, and enqueue their children. Repeat until the queue is empty.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Each node visited once</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Queue holds up to one level</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Level Order BFS</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="fn">levelOrder</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){
        <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="kw">if</span>(root==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> res;
        <span class="tp">Queue</span>&lt;<span class="tp">TreeNode</span>&gt; q=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">LinkedList</span>&lt;&gt;(); q.offer(root);
        <span class="kw">while</span>(!q.isEmpty()){
            <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; level=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
            <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=q.size();i&gt;<span class="nm">0</span>;i--){
                <span class="tp">TreeNode</span> n=q.poll(); level.add(n.val);
                <span class="kw">if</span>(n.left!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                q.offer(n.left);
            } <span class="kw">if</span>(n.right!=<span class="kw">null</span>) {
                q.offer(n.right);
            }
            }
            res.add(level);
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> res;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#110</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Balanced Binary Tree</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">DFS with Sentinel Value</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Bottom-Up Height Check</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Bottom-Up DFS with -1 Sentinel</strong>Return the height from each subtree. If a subtree is unbalanced (height difference > 1), propagate -1 upward to short-circuit. Avoids recomputing heights — O(n) instead of O(n log n).</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>Single bottom-up pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(h)</td><td>Recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">isBalanced</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> root){<span class="kw">return</span> <span class="fn">h</span>(root)!=-<span class="nm">1</span>;}
    <span class="kw">int</span> <span class="fn">h</span>(<span class="tp">TreeNode</span> n){
        <span class="kw">if</span>(n==<span class="kw">null</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> <span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">int</span> l=<span class="fn">h</span>(n.left); <span class="kw">if</span>(l==-<span class="nm">1</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> -<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">int</span> r=<span class="fn">h</span>(n.right);<span class="kw">if</span>(r==-<span class="nm">1</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> -<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">return</span> <span class="tp">Math</span>.abs(l-r)&gt;<span class="nm">1</span> ? -<span class="nm">1</span> : <span class="nm">1</span>+<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(l,r);
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

