  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#39</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Combination Sum</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Backtracking</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Explore-Choose-Unchoose</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Backtracking with Reuse</strong>At each step choose a candidate (allowing reuse at the same index). Recurse with reduced remaining. If remaining = 0, record result. Prune when candidate &gt; remaining. Undo choice before next iteration.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n^(T/M))</td><td>T=target, M=min candidate</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(T/M)</td><td>Max recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span><span class="code-title">Combination Sum — Backtracking</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="fn">combinationSum</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] c,<span class="kw">int</span> t){
        <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
        <span class="fn">bt</span>(c,t,<span class="nm">0</span>,<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;(),res); <span class="kw">return</span> res;
    }
    <span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">bt</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] c,<span class="kw">int</span> rem,<span class="kw">int</span> start,<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt; cur,<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; res){
        <span class="kw">if</span>(rem==<span class="nm">0</span>){res.add(<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;(cur));<span class="kw">return</span>;}
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=start;i&lt;c.length;i++){
