}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#46</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Permutations</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Backtracking</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Used-Array State Tracking</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Backtracking with Boolean Used Array</strong>At each position, try every unused number. Mark it as used, recurse, then unmark (backtrack). When current list reaches nums.length, a complete permutation is found.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n × n!)</td><td>n! permutations, each length n</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Recursion depth + used array</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="fn">permute</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
