  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#51</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">N-Queens</h3><span class="tag tag-red">Hard</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Backtracking</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Constraint Propagation via Sets</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Backtracking with Column/Diagonal Sets</strong>Place one queen per row. Track occupied columns and two diagonal directions (row-col, row+col) using HashSets. If a column is safe, place the queen, recurse, and remove. Classic constraint satisfaction backtracking.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n!)</td><td>Worst-case placements</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n²)</td><td>Board + 3 sets</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">String</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="fn">solveNQueens</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n){
        <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">String</span>&gt;&gt; res=<span class="kw">new</span> <span class="tp">ArrayList</span>&lt;&gt;();
