  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#90</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Subsets II</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Backtracking</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Sort + Skip Duplicates</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Backtracking with Duplicate Pruning</strong>Sort the input. In the backtracking loop, if <code>i &gt; start &amp;&amp; nums[i] == nums[i-1]</code>, skip — this prevents choosing the same value at the same recursion depth twice, eliminating duplicate subsets.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n × 2ⁿ)</td><td>Subsets with dedup</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>Recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public</span> <span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">List</span>&lt;<span class="tp">Integer</span>&gt;&gt; <span class="fn">subsetsWithDup</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
