}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#37</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Sudoku Solver</h3><span class="tag tag-red">Hard</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Backtracking</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Constraint Checking (Row/Col/Box)</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Backtracking with Constraint Validation</strong>Find the next empty cell. Try digits 1–9. Validate against row, column, and 3×3 box constraints. If valid, place the digit and recurse. If no digit works, backtrack (restore '.').</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(9^m)</td><td>m = empty cells (bounded by 81)</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(m)</td><td>Recursion depth</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public void</span> <span class="fn">solveSudoku</span>(<span class="kw">char</span>[][] board){<span class="fn">solve</span>(board);}
    <span class="kw">boolean</span> <span class="fn">solve</span>(<span class="kw">char</span>[][] b){
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;<span class="nm">9</span>;i++) <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">0</span>;j&lt;<span class="nm">9</span>;j++){
