  <h2 class="section-heading" id="dp"><span class="section-icon">DP</span> Dynamic Programming</h2>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#70</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Climbing Stairs</h3><span class="tag tag-green">Easy</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (1D)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Fibonacci / Bottom-Up DP</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Space-Optimized 1D DP</strong>dp[n] = dp[n-1] + dp[n-2] (can come from 1 or 2 steps below). Reduce to two variables — no array needed. This is essentially Fibonacci starting at (1, 2).</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>One loop</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Two rolling variables</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">climbStairs</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n){
        <span class="kw">if</span>(n&lt;=<span class="nm">2</span>)<span class="kw">return</span> n;
        <span class="kw">int</span> a=<span class="nm">1</span>,b=<span class="nm">2</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">3</span>;i&lt;=n;i++){<span class="kw">int</span> c=a+b;a=b;b=c;}
        <span class="kw">return</span> b;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#198</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">House Robber</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (1D)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Decision DP: Rob vs Skip</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Rolling Variables DP</strong>At each house: max(skip it = prev1, rob it = prev2 + current). Use two rolling variables to track the last two states. No array needed — O(1) space.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n)</td><td>One pass</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(1)</td><td>Rolling two variables</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">rob</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
        <span class="kw">int</span> a=<span class="nm">0</span>,b=<span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n:nums){<span class="kw">int</span> c=<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(b,a+n);a=b;b=c;}
        <span class="kw">return</span> b;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#322</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Coin Change</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (Unbounded Knapsack)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Bottom-Up DP Array</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — Bottom-Up Coin DP</strong>dp[i] = min coins for amount i. For each amount 1..target, try every coin: dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i-coin]+1). Initialize dp[0]=0, rest=infinity. Unbounded knapsack variant.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(amount × coins)</td><td>Two nested loops</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(amount)</td><td>dp array size</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">coinChange</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] coins,<span class="kw">int</span> amount){
        <span class="kw">int</span>[] dp=<span class="kw">new int</span>[amount+<span class="nm">1</span>];
        <span class="tp">Arrays</span>.fill(dp,amount+<span class="nm">1</span>); dp[<span class="nm">0</span>]=<span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">1</span>;i&lt;=amount;i++)
            <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> c:coins) <span class="kw">if</span>(c&lt;=i) {
                dp[i]=<span class="tp">Math</span>.min(dp[i],dp[i-c]+<span class="nm">1</span>);
            }
        <span class="kw">return</span> dp[amount]&gt;amount?-<span class="nm">1</span>:dp[amount];
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#300</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Longest Increasing Subsequence</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (1D)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Subsequence DP (O(n²) / O(n log n) Patience Sort)</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — DP with All-Previous Comparison</strong>dp[i] = length of LIS ending at index i. For each i, scan all j &lt; i where nums[j] &lt; nums[i]: dp[i] = max(dp[j]+1). For O(n log n), use patience sorting with binary search on a tails array.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n²)</td><td>Standard DP; O(n log n) with patience sort</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(n)</td><td>dp array</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">lengthOfLIS</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
        <span class="kw">int</span>[] dp=<span class="kw">new int</span>[nums.length]; <span class="tp">Arrays</span>.fill(dp,<span class="nm">1</span>); <span class="kw">int</span> max=<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">1</span>;i&lt;nums.length;i++){
            <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">0</span>;j&lt;i;j++) <span class="kw">if</span>(nums[j]&lt;nums[i]) {
                dp[i]=<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(dp[i],dp[j]+<span class="nm">1</span>);
            }
            max=<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(max,dp[i]);
        }
        <span class="kw">return</span> max;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#1143</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Longest Common Subsequence</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (2D)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Grid DP / LCS</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — 2D DP Table</strong>dp[i][j] = LCS of text1[0..i-1] and text2[0..j-1]. Match: dp[i-1][j-1]+1. No match: max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]). Reducible to O(min(m,n)) space with rolling row.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m × n)</td><td>Fill entire DP table</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(m × n)</td><td>Reducible to O(min(m,n))</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">longestCommonSubsequence</span>(<span class="tp">String</span> t1,<span class="tp">String</span> t2){
        <span class="kw">int</span> m=t1.length(),n=t2.length();
        <span class="kw">int</span>[][] dp=<span class="kw">new int</span>[m+<span class="nm">1</span>][n+<span class="nm">1</span>];
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">1</span>;i&lt;=m;i++) <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">1</span>;j&lt;=n;j++)
            dp[i][j]=t1.charAt(i-<span class="nm">1</span>)==t2.charAt(j-<span class="nm">1</span>)?dp[i-<span class="nm">1</span>][j-<span class="nm">1</span>]+<span class="nm">1</span>:<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(dp[i-<span class="nm">1</span>][j],dp[i][j-<span class="nm">1</span>]);
        <span class="kw">return</span> dp[m][n];
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#62</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Unique Paths</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (2D)</span><span class="tag tag-teal">Grid Path Counting</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — 2D DP Grid</strong>dp[i][j] = ways to reach (i,j) = dp[i-1][j] + dp[i][j-1]. First row and column are all 1s (only one direction). Reducible to 1D array.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m × n)</td><td>Fill grid</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(m × n)</td><td>Reducible to O(n)</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">uniquePaths</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> m,<span class="kw">int</span> n){
        <span class="kw">int</span>[][] dp=<span class="kw">new int</span>[m][n];
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">0</span>;i&lt;m;i++)dp[i][<span class="nm">0</span>]=<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">0</span>;j&lt;n;j++)dp[<span class="nm">0</span>][j]=<span class="nm">1</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">1</span>;i&lt;m;i++) <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">1</span>;j&lt;n;j++) dp[i][j]=dp[i-<span class="nm">1</span>][j]+dp[i][j-<span class="nm">1</span>];
        <span class="kw">return</span> dp[m-<span class="nm">1</span>][n-<span class="nm">1</span>];
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#718</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Maximum Length of Repeated Subarray</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (2D)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Substring Match DP</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — 2D Matching DP</strong>dp[i][j] = length of common subarray ending at nums1[i-1] and nums2[j-1]. If elements match: dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]+1. Unlike LCS, reset to 0 on mismatch. Track global max.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(m × n)</td><td>Fill table</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(m × n)</td><td>DP table</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public int</span> <span class="fn">findLength</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] n1,<span class="kw">int</span>[] n2){
        <span class="kw">int</span> m=n1.length,n=n2.length,max=<span class="nm">0</span>;
        <span class="kw">int</span>[][] dp=<span class="kw">new int</span>[m+<span class="nm">1</span>][n+<span class="nm">1</span>];
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i=<span class="nm">1</span>;i&lt;=m;i++) <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=<span class="nm">1</span>;j&lt;=n;j++)
            <span class="kw">if</span>(n1[i-<span class="nm">1</span>]==n2[j-<span class="nm">1</span>]) {
                max=<span class="tp">Math</span>.max(max,dp[i][j]=dp[i-<span class="nm">1</span>][j-<span class="nm">1</span>]+<span class="nm">1</span>);
            }
        <span class="kw">return</span> max;
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

  <div class="problem-card"><div class="problem-card-header"><span class="problem-number">#416</span><h3 class="problem-heading" style="margin:0">Partition Equal Subset Sum</h3><span class="tag tag-orange">Medium</span></div><div class="problem-card-body"><div class="technique-row"><span class="technique-label">🎯 Technique</span><span class="tag tag-blue">Dynamic Programming (0/1 Knapsack)</span><span class="tag tag-purple">Boolean Subset Sum DP</span></div><div class="panel info"><span class="panel-icon">💡</span><div class="panel-content"><strong>Approach — 0/1 Knapsack (Subset Sum)</strong>Reduce to: can we pick a subset summing to total/2? Use a boolean dp[]. dp[j] = true if sum j is achievable. Iterate backwards to avoid using each element twice.</div></div><table class="complexity-table"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Complexity</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Time</td><td class="complexity-time">O(n × sum)</td><td>0/1 knapsack</td></tr><tr><td>Space</td><td class="complexity-space">O(sum)</td><td>1D boolean DP</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="code-block"><div class="code-header"><span class="code-lang">Java</span></div><pre><span class="kw">class</span> <span class="tp">Solution</span> {
    <span class="kw">public boolean</span> <span class="fn">canPartition</span>(<span class="kw">int</span>[] nums){
        <span class="kw">int</span> sum=<span class="nm">0</span>; <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n:nums)sum+=n;
        <span class="kw">if</span>(sum%<span class="nm">2</span>!=<span class="nm">0</span>)<span class="kw">return false</span>;
        <span class="kw">int</span> t=sum/<span class="nm">2</span>; <span class="kw">boolean</span>[] dp=<span class="kw">new boolean</span>[t+<span class="nm">1</span>]; dp[<span class="nm">0</span>]=<span class="kw">true</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> n:nums) <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j=t;j&gt;=n;j--) dp[j]|=dp[j-n];
        <span class="kw">return</span> dp[t];
    }
}</pre></div></div></div>

